1
00:00:02,804 --> 00:00:05,174
As a child, I thought

2
00:00:05,174 --> 00:00:08,614
your mother is just your mother.

3
00:00:09,084 --> 00:00:10,884
A teacher is just a teacher,

4
00:00:10,884 --> 00:00:17,024
and a police officer is just
a police officer and nothing more.

5
00:00:17,024 --> 00:00:23,184
And celebrities were just celebrities.
They were different from me.

6
00:00:24,864 --> 00:00:26,834
And I still felt that way, even now,
at twenty.

7
00:00:50,894 --> 00:00:53,924
When I was darkness at that time

8
00:00:53,924 --> 00:00:56,764
With trembling lips

9
00:00:56,764 --> 00:00:59,854
In a corner of a room I cry

10
00:01:02,264 --> 00:01:04,934
The more I struggle

11
00:01:04,934 --> 00:01:07,774
The more this wound deepens

12
00:01:07,774 --> 00:01:10,934
The broken promise hurt me

13
00:01:13,584 --> 00:01:15,674
Nobody can save me

14
00:01:16,214 --> 00:01:18,854
God, I have only one request

15
00:01:18,854 --> 00:01:22,484
Stop tearing apart my love

16
00:01:22,884 --> 00:01:25,824
I need your love

17
00:01:25,824 --> 00:01:29,054
I'm a broken rose

18
00:01:29,124 --> 00:01:31,994
Sorrow tumbling down is your song

19
00:01:31,994 --> 00:01:34,164
All alone with nowhere to go in my life

20
00:01:34,164 --> 00:01:36,934
I need your love

21
00:01:36,934 --> 00:01:40,244
I'm a broken rose

22
00:01:40,244 --> 00:01:43,174
Oh baby, help me from frozen pain

23
00:01:43,174 --> 00:01:47,134
With your smile, your eyes,
and sing me, just for me

24
00:01:47,884 --> 00:01:50,114
I wanna need your love

25
00:01:50,714 --> 00:01:53,344
I'm a broken rose

26
00:01:53,524 --> 00:01:55,684
I wanna need your love

27
00:02:07,734 --> 00:02:11,034
But this is such coincidence.
I'm surprised.

28
00:02:11,674 --> 00:02:12,634
Yes.

29
00:02:13,004 --> 00:02:16,564
Well, surprised doesn't even
begin to explain how I felt.

30
00:02:17,074 --> 00:02:20,234
So, where should we go?
Do you mind if we get home late?

31
00:02:20,844 --> 00:02:22,904
Tomorrow's Saturday. You don't
hafta work tomorrow, do you?

32
00:02:23,654 --> 00:02:24,514
Yes.

33
00:02:24,514 --> 00:02:26,544
What I wanna know is...
Is this reality?

34
00:02:27,524 --> 00:02:29,214
Don't be so nervous.

35
00:02:29,624 --> 00:02:32,094
Yes. I'm sorry. It's just...

36
00:02:32,494 --> 00:02:34,894
It's fine. There's no need to apologize.

37
00:02:35,064 --> 00:02:37,654
Yes. But... Oh boy,
what am I gonna do?

38
00:02:37,964 --> 00:02:40,294
Now you're making me nervous.

39
00:02:40,534 --> 00:02:41,964
Huh?! Why?

40
00:02:42,204 --> 00:02:45,474
Because, well, I never imagined
in my wildest dreams

41
00:02:45,474 --> 00:02:48,564
that I'd meet you in this manner.
I wasn't prepared for this.

42
00:02:48,804 --> 00:02:50,634
That's my line.

43
00:02:51,074 --> 00:02:53,564
But I was thinking how
nice it would be to see you again.

44
00:02:54,444 --> 00:02:56,104
No way. That's impossible.

45
00:02:56,544 --> 00:03:00,484
No, really. Otherwise,
I wouldn't have called you.

46
00:03:00,784 --> 00:03:03,254
The truth is, I'm terrible at
doing the small things.

47
00:03:04,194 --> 00:03:06,214
Yeah, this has to be a dream.

48
00:03:06,994 --> 00:03:09,514
Because in reality,
these things just don't happen.

49
00:03:10,194 --> 00:03:13,064
Even if they do, at least there's
no way it would happen to me.

50
00:03:28,284 --> 00:03:31,444
Green light already?
What a restless traffic light.

51
00:03:33,754 --> 00:03:34,724
And so am I.

52
00:03:37,524 --> 00:03:40,154
He seems to be quite the player.

53
00:03:43,094 --> 00:03:46,534
That dream-like kiss
abruptly woke me up from my dream.

54
00:03:47,704 --> 00:03:51,964
This is not a fairytale. There's no way
Takumi could be a prince.

55
00:03:53,004 --> 00:03:54,974
He'll sleep with me once
and dump me.

56
00:03:56,104 --> 00:03:57,134
Wait here.

57
00:04:03,014 --> 00:04:04,714
Should I go home right this moment?

58
00:04:05,984 --> 00:04:08,284
I didn't plan for this to happen.

59
00:04:09,454 --> 00:04:11,084
Hey, isn't he that guy from Trapnest?

60
00:04:11,294 --> 00:04:13,754
Wow! Cool! He's so tall!

61
00:04:14,424 --> 00:04:17,454
Then why did I get into his car?

62
00:04:18,494 --> 00:04:22,334
I'm not that foolish to believe he would
even think of making me his girlfriend.

63
00:04:23,404 --> 00:04:28,464
And I'm not that naïve to think this'll
end after a drive and dinner.

64
00:04:29,504 --> 00:04:33,134
There must be a part of me
that was hoping for this.

65
00:04:34,984 --> 00:04:39,074
There's no need to hesitate. I'll never
be in a situation like this again, ever.

66
00:04:39,784 --> 00:04:43,954
I don't have a boyfriend now,
so there's no reason to feel guilty.

67
00:04:44,554 --> 00:04:47,614
Think of this as creating
a once in a lifetime special memory.

68
00:04:48,864 --> 00:04:49,824
Sorry to keep you waiting.

69
00:04:55,664 --> 00:04:57,234
- He's from Trapnest...
- Ren?

70
00:04:57,234 --> 00:04:58,394
No, the long haired guy.

71
00:04:58,874 --> 00:05:03,394
Th-They saw us. And what's worse,
while he had his arm around me.

72
00:05:04,644 --> 00:05:07,444
We'll be in the tabloids.
We'll be on TV.

73
00:05:08,114 --> 00:05:09,634
I'm hungry.

74
00:05:10,514 --> 00:05:12,214
Um... Mr. Takumi...

75
00:05:12,384 --> 00:05:13,354
Mr?

76
00:05:13,684 --> 00:05:15,914
But you've always
just called me Takumi.

77
00:05:16,154 --> 00:05:18,314
Well that's true, but...
that's not the point.

78
00:05:18,424 --> 00:05:20,024
It may not be something
for me to point out,

79
00:05:20,024 --> 00:05:21,424
but aren't you concerned

80
00:05:21,424 --> 00:05:23,364
of the risks of being seen
entering a hotel with a girl?

81
00:05:23,564 --> 00:05:26,534
At the least, perhaps you should
wear some kind of complete disguise.

82
00:05:27,104 --> 00:05:28,694
Some kind of complete disguise?

83
00:05:29,634 --> 00:05:31,964
But if I wore a costume,
I'd stand out even more.

84
00:05:33,174 --> 00:05:35,644
You'd look good in one!
This is no time to be joking!

85
00:05:35,644 --> 00:05:36,544
What's with this guy?
He's pretty funny!
You'd look good in one!
This is no time to be joking!

86
00:05:36,804 --> 00:05:38,204
Not to worry.

87
00:05:38,674 --> 00:05:41,404
The entertainment reporters are too
busy to be following my every step.

88
00:05:41,714 --> 00:05:44,214
Our band keeps a lid
on our public appearances,

89
00:05:44,214 --> 00:05:46,714
so people don't recognize us enough
that we need to be overly cautious.

90
00:05:46,714 --> 00:05:49,954
What are you saying?
Trapnest is really famous.

91
00:05:50,324 --> 00:05:53,554
I guess Reira is.
She may need a costume.

92
00:05:53,824 --> 00:05:56,094
I'd say all four of you share
about the same level of fame.

93
00:05:56,294 --> 00:05:58,024
You think that because you're a fan.

94
00:05:59,064 --> 00:06:01,054
The general public may
also recognize Ren, but that's it.

95
00:06:01,504 --> 00:06:02,634
Naoki and I are known as

96
00:06:02,634 --> 00:06:04,434
the blonde guy
and the long haired guy.

97
00:06:04,604 --> 00:06:07,404
That's not true! You're number one
in my book, Takumi!

98
00:06:12,844 --> 00:06:16,214
I'll bet he thinks of me as
a foolish, easy woman.

99
00:06:17,254 --> 00:06:19,444
But that's basically
the type of woman I am.

100
00:06:20,484 --> 00:06:21,584
With all I've been through,

101
00:06:21,584 --> 00:06:24,054
I thought I had become
more cautious towards men.

102
00:06:24,924 --> 00:06:27,224
But nothing's changed since that summer
back when I was seventeen.

103
00:06:28,794 --> 00:06:32,464
If only I could remain high
on this moment of happiness,

104
00:06:32,464 --> 00:06:34,594
I wouldn't even care about tomorrow.

105
00:06:36,404 --> 00:06:37,394
What's this?

106
00:06:37,534 --> 00:06:38,674
Awesome!

107
00:06:38,674 --> 00:06:40,224
It's huge! There are two rooms!

108
00:06:40,604 --> 00:06:42,334
So pretty! It's like a castle.

109
00:06:42,504 --> 00:06:43,494
Would this happen to be...

110
00:06:44,144 --> 00:06:45,444
A suite room?

111
00:06:46,844 --> 00:06:48,174
Do you like it?

112
00:06:50,314 --> 00:06:53,144
Right now, I'm so happy
I could just die.

113
00:06:53,384 --> 00:06:55,254
If I could die here,
I'd die a happy woman.

114
00:06:55,524 --> 00:06:57,854
If you must die, do it in bed.

115
00:06:58,994 --> 00:07:01,054
But before that let's
get something to eat.

116
00:07:02,524 --> 00:07:04,494
Choose anything you like.

117
00:07:04,794 --> 00:07:07,634
Huh? Are you suggesting
that we eat in the room?

118
00:07:07,804 --> 00:07:10,064
Oh, if you prefer not to,
we can dine out.

119
00:07:10,164 --> 00:07:13,534
No, I've dreamed of
ordering room service in a hotel!

120
00:07:13,944 --> 00:07:15,804
Their specialty is duck.

121
00:07:15,804 --> 00:07:18,114
Duck? I've never had duck.

122
00:07:18,114 --> 00:07:21,444
Really? Never? It's great.
Then how about foie gras?

123
00:07:21,444 --> 00:07:23,274
I've totally never had foie gras.

124
00:07:23,584 --> 00:07:25,074
Then should we get some caviar too?

125
00:07:25,154 --> 00:07:26,204
Yay!

126
00:07:26,454 --> 00:07:29,384
Why not take a shower
and relax until the food arrives?

127
00:07:30,084 --> 00:07:31,854
There's a bathrobe, so use that.

128
00:07:32,494 --> 00:07:34,724
Yes. A bathrobe?

129
00:07:35,464 --> 00:07:37,824
He knows this place
like it were his own castle.

130
00:07:38,734 --> 00:07:41,894
These are brand name cosmetics.
I wonder if I can take them home.

131
00:07:44,834 --> 00:07:49,874
I'm sure tons of foolish girls like me
approach Takumi,

132
00:07:49,874 --> 00:07:52,204
and I'm no more than
one of the many.

133
00:07:52,614 --> 00:07:56,214
But if I'm here, well aware of that,
there should be nothing wrong

134
00:07:56,214 --> 00:07:58,914
with me spending one night
to purposely enjoy a dream, right?

135
00:08:00,684 --> 00:08:01,674
Delicious!

136
00:08:01,824 --> 00:08:04,894
Isn't it? But to me,
that food you prepared

137
00:08:04,894 --> 00:08:06,414
was better than this, Nana.

138
00:08:07,364 --> 00:08:08,694
That's impossible.

139
00:08:08,964 --> 00:08:12,494
No, I'm serious. While on tour,
we always eat out

140
00:08:12,494 --> 00:08:13,654
and I get sick and tired of it.

141
00:08:13,934 --> 00:08:16,804
By the way, you're back on your tour
starting tomorrow, right?

142
00:08:17,004 --> 00:08:18,694
Are you okay for time?

143
00:08:19,034 --> 00:08:20,304
Not a problem.

144
00:08:20,644 --> 00:08:23,914
We leave early in the morning
so I hafta leave during the evening,

145
00:08:23,914 --> 00:08:26,074
but you can take it easy
and spend the night here, Nana.

146
00:08:27,714 --> 00:08:29,644
What? He's gonna leave?

147
00:08:30,714 --> 00:08:34,374
Come on, don't make such a sad face.
It'll make it hard for me to go.

148
00:08:34,524 --> 00:08:36,924
Oh, no, I'm sorry. That'll be fine.

149
00:08:37,084 --> 00:08:39,854
I don't mind.
I'm not thinking of anything as dreamy

150
00:08:39,854 --> 00:08:42,484
as keeping you here with me
until the morning.

151
00:08:50,204 --> 00:08:51,494
Once the tour is over...

152
00:08:53,374 --> 00:08:54,934
I'll come directly to see you.

153
00:08:55,504 --> 00:08:57,274
When I do, would you mind
cooking for me again?

154
00:09:00,314 --> 00:09:01,474
I mustn't take him seriously.

155
00:09:02,744 --> 00:09:05,044
It's okay. I'm not that stupid.

156
00:09:06,014 --> 00:09:08,504
I guess I am different from
when I was seventeen.

157
00:09:09,684 --> 00:09:10,844
Thank you for the meal.

158
00:09:11,654 --> 00:09:14,094
Then I'll go take a quick shower.

159
00:09:14,594 --> 00:09:16,454
You can warm up and wait for me.

160
00:09:16,594 --> 00:09:18,794
You are really impatient, Takumi.

161
00:09:19,094 --> 00:09:21,104
I'm not thinking of
quickly running home

162
00:09:21,104 --> 00:09:23,624
after eating all that I can.
So take your time.

163
00:09:26,004 --> 00:09:27,904
But I can't help but wonder

164
00:09:27,904 --> 00:09:30,934
how many women Takumi's slept with,
using this method.

165
00:09:31,544 --> 00:09:34,314
Is he really satisfied
with commoners like me

166
00:09:34,314 --> 00:09:35,544
who have little money and no skills?

167
00:09:37,984 --> 00:09:39,614
I've gotta warm up. Gotta warm up.

168
00:09:40,924 --> 00:09:42,974
The phone.
Should I turn the power off?

169
00:09:44,154 --> 00:09:45,984
090... who is it?

170
00:09:47,224 --> 00:09:48,194
Hello.

171
00:09:48,194 --> 00:09:49,354
Hachiko!

172
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,934
You're late, so I'm getting worried.

173
00:09:52,194 --> 00:09:54,224
Where are you wandering
at this hour?

174
00:09:54,664 --> 00:09:57,504
Nana? Huh? Whose phone
are you calling from?

175
00:09:57,674 --> 00:09:59,074
Mine.

176
00:09:59,074 --> 00:10:00,564
So you bought a cell phone.

177
00:10:00,744 --> 00:10:03,074
Well, Ren bought me one.
He insisted I carry one.

178
00:10:03,604 --> 00:10:05,174
Is that so? That's great.

179
00:10:05,174 --> 00:10:08,874
But I don't understand how to use it.
Like how to email.

180
00:10:09,144 --> 00:10:10,414
Doesn't it have a manual?

181
00:10:10,414 --> 00:10:12,384
It's thick, so I don't wanna read it.

182
00:10:13,484 --> 00:10:15,524
I thought I'd have you teach me
when you got home,

183
00:10:15,524 --> 00:10:16,574
so I've been waiting.

184
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:18,854
But unless yours is
the same model as mine,

185
00:10:18,854 --> 00:10:20,054
the functions are
gonna be different.

186
00:10:20,124 --> 00:10:21,094
Is that so?

187
00:10:21,524 --> 00:10:24,224
Then hurry home, read the manual
and teach me how to use it.

188
00:10:25,694 --> 00:10:27,224
What about Ren?
Have Ren teach you.

189
00:10:27,564 --> 00:10:29,124
The person who bought that for you
should be responsible.

190
00:10:29,464 --> 00:10:30,834
Ren left a short while ago.

191
00:10:31,934 --> 00:10:34,734
Of course. He has to leave
early tomorrow morning.

192
00:10:35,774 --> 00:10:36,904
I'm surprised you know that.

193
00:10:37,544 --> 00:10:39,704
B-Because Ren said so yesterday!

194
00:10:39,844 --> 00:10:40,744
Yeah?

195
00:10:40,744 --> 00:10:42,144
Mhm! He totally did!

196
00:10:42,284 --> 00:10:45,444
So, where are you now?
When are you coming home?

197
00:10:45,784 --> 00:10:48,254
Well... um, sorry... maybe not today.

198
00:10:48,724 --> 00:10:51,284
I'm at a friend's place,
and I might stay over.

199
00:10:51,624 --> 00:10:54,364
Really? So there are friends
who are willing to have you stay over,

200
00:10:54,364 --> 00:10:55,624
knowing how troublesome you are.

201
00:10:57,224 --> 00:10:57,934
A guy?

202
00:10:57,934 --> 00:10:59,624
N-No! I-I'm at Jun-chan's!

203
00:11:01,164 --> 00:11:03,134
I'm joking. Don't take it so seriously.

204
00:11:03,564 --> 00:11:05,964
All right. I'll study my cell phone
on my own.

205
00:11:06,404 --> 00:11:07,564
Say "Hi" to Junko for me.

206
00:11:09,674 --> 00:11:11,044
I can't tell Nana.

207
00:11:12,714 --> 00:11:13,874
I don't want her to know.

208
00:11:15,044 --> 00:11:18,414
If she finds out that I'm knowingly
being such an easy woman,

209
00:11:18,414 --> 00:11:19,854
she'll never look at me the same.

210
00:11:22,384 --> 00:11:23,374
But you know, Nana...

211
00:11:24,154 --> 00:11:27,684
The truth is, I too wanna love someone
as diligently as you do.

212
00:11:28,664 --> 00:11:32,654
Like you and Ren, I too wanna have
that connection with someone.

213
00:11:34,034 --> 00:11:37,464
Hey, Nana. The truth is,
I'm not at all okay.

214
00:11:38,604 --> 00:11:42,064
I'd hate to be dumped by Takumi
after a one night stand.

215
00:11:42,944 --> 00:11:48,244
What should I do? I'm scared, Nana.
But I can't run away at this stage.

216
00:11:48,984 --> 00:11:51,044
I can't bring myself to tell him
I want him to love me.

217
00:11:54,524 --> 00:11:58,284
This isn't good. I could end up
feeling hurt all over again.

218
00:12:00,694 --> 00:12:01,264
If anyone asks, I'm staying
at your place tonight.
Nana

219
00:12:01,264 --> 00:12:03,194
If anyone asks, I'm staying
at your place tonight.
Nana
Say. What do you think
of this alibi creation?

220
00:12:03,194 --> 00:12:04,354
Say. What do you think
of this alibi creation?

221
00:12:05,364 --> 00:12:07,664
Nana's roommate is a woman, right?

222
00:12:08,034 --> 00:12:09,004
Mhm.

223
00:12:09,234 --> 00:12:12,134
But that woman is more handsome
and manly than your average man.

224
00:12:12,534 --> 00:12:16,264
Nana seems to have a serious crush
on her. Maybe those two are a couple.

225
00:12:17,304 --> 00:12:18,934
But never mind that.

226
00:12:19,044 --> 00:12:20,014
Really?

227
00:12:20,174 --> 00:12:21,314
There's something fishy about this.

228
00:12:21,314 --> 00:12:22,284
About what?

229
00:12:22,584 --> 00:12:24,944
Jun-chan. You feeling drunk?

230
00:12:25,914 --> 00:12:28,214
It's the smell of a new man.

231
00:12:28,724 --> 00:12:29,724
I just hope she hasn't been

232
00:12:29,724 --> 00:12:32,384
caught by some guy so terrible
she can't even tell her roommate.

233
00:12:34,054 --> 00:12:37,114
Takumi's hair was so long,
it showered my body.

234
00:12:38,234 --> 00:12:43,724
As I let it caress me, I laid there
wishing he would always keep it long.

235
00:12:46,074 --> 00:12:49,334
Even though I may
never touch it again.

236
00:13:10,594 --> 00:13:12,964
He said it'll be hard for him to go,

237
00:13:12,964 --> 00:13:14,764
but once he's done,
he's quick to leave.

238
00:13:15,834 --> 00:13:19,534
Even his departure is hurried.
Such a busy prince.

239
00:13:20,874 --> 00:13:24,744
I should go home too. I'm done with
playing a make-believe princess.

240
00:13:27,244 --> 00:13:32,084
What? I can't. I've got no strength.
It's as if I have no bones.

241
00:13:37,694 --> 00:13:41,644
I have to pull myself together.
I must quickly return to reality.

242
00:13:42,794 --> 00:13:45,784
In the morning, I've gotta look for
whatever job's available.

243
00:13:46,364 --> 00:13:48,734
And this time, I'm gonna
take my work seriously.

244
00:13:50,934 --> 00:13:53,764
Damn! The last train left long ago.

245
00:13:54,344 --> 00:13:56,904
And I don't have enough money to
take a taxi home from the city center.

246
00:13:58,214 --> 00:14:00,074
I might as well spend the night here.

247
00:14:00,884 --> 00:14:02,884
It's likely a once in
a lifetime opportunity

248
