270
00:15:21,494 --> 00:15:23,484
That's not what I'm asking.

271
00:15:23,794 --> 00:15:25,384
But you wanted to know.

272
00:15:25,594 --> 00:15:28,394
So he really did become one,
even with that look.

273
00:15:29,204 --> 00:15:30,164
Even with that look?

274
00:15:30,904 --> 00:15:34,064
So his dream came true. I'm glad.

275
00:15:34,844 --> 00:15:38,614
He had already passed
the qualification exam

276
00:15:38,614 --> 00:15:40,004
during his fourth year in university.

277
00:15:40,544 --> 00:15:41,704
That's really something,
don't you think?

278
00:15:42,884 --> 00:15:44,014
Is that unusual?!

279
00:15:44,014 --> 00:15:46,284
Would you stay outta this,
blonde guy?

280
00:15:47,384 --> 00:15:50,354
But now he's moved to Tokyo
because of his band.

281
00:15:50,684 --> 00:15:52,584
So isn't his dream to become
a professional musician?

282
00:15:52,854 --> 00:15:54,914
Huh? Moved to Tokyo?
Because of his band?

283
00:15:55,024 --> 00:15:57,684
The band he and Ren had
before Ren joined us.

284
00:15:58,234 --> 00:16:00,964
They found a new bassist,

285
00:16:00,964 --> 00:16:02,664
and have been giving it
some serious effort.

286
00:16:04,134 --> 00:16:05,264
What's this?

287
00:16:05,434 --> 00:16:07,604
After snobbishly telling me repeatedly

288
00:16:07,604 --> 00:16:10,904
that bands are nothing more than
a hobby? I don't get him.

289
00:16:11,074 --> 00:16:13,634
Yeah. Leaves a bad taste, doesn't it?
Want me to rough him up?

290
00:16:14,814 --> 00:16:17,504
What made him decide
to do this now?

291
00:16:21,754 --> 00:16:22,914
Yasu!

292
00:16:26,624 --> 00:16:27,754
Why are you smoking?!

293
00:16:28,624 --> 00:16:30,324
Never mind, continue smoking.

294
00:16:30,964 --> 00:16:35,624
I know very well that you
only stop smoking in front of me.

295
00:16:36,564 --> 00:16:38,794
You're only considerate like that
on the surface.

296
00:16:39,274 --> 00:16:41,104
But then you secretly do stuff
in the shadows.

297
00:16:41,844 --> 00:16:43,234
What else are you hiding?!

298
00:16:43,744 --> 00:16:45,074
Nothing really.

299
00:16:45,274 --> 00:16:48,904
You have too many secrets!
I'm really pissed off, you know!

300
00:16:49,284 --> 00:16:51,774
Why didn't you say anything
about you and Reira?!

301
00:16:52,214 --> 00:16:53,704
Oh, that. I'm sorry.

302
00:16:54,684 --> 00:16:57,454
"Were you that impressed
by Reira's voice?"

303
00:16:57,854 --> 00:16:59,114
It's not funny!

304
00:16:59,494 --> 00:17:00,454
I said I'm sorry.

305
00:17:04,194 --> 00:17:06,354
She was really great, that Reira.

306
00:17:07,234 --> 00:17:10,254
I felt so defeated.
I'm no match for her.

307
00:17:11,174 --> 00:17:12,434
Was she like that since the old days?

308
00:17:13,634 --> 00:17:15,734
Is that what you call a genius?

309
00:17:19,344 --> 00:17:20,314
I guess.

310
00:17:21,384 --> 00:17:23,614
But she has defined abs.

311
00:17:26,154 --> 00:17:29,014
Hmm... You sure are well informed.

312
00:17:31,554 --> 00:17:34,044
Where's Hachi?
Isn't she coming today?

313
00:17:34,394 --> 00:17:36,254
Nobu, that's all you've been saying.

314
00:17:36,564 --> 00:17:37,424
Huh?

315
00:17:37,424 --> 00:17:39,234
Hey, Nobuo.
Are you in love with Hachiko?

316
00:17:39,234 --> 00:17:40,494
No, I, ah...

317
00:17:40,594 --> 00:17:42,794
It's just that, it's kinda lonely
without our regular audience.

318
00:17:43,104 --> 00:17:44,864
But Hachi's only one person.

319
00:17:45,074 --> 00:17:48,404
I want to perform live!

320
00:17:48,404 --> 00:17:50,934
I need to release this tension!

321
00:17:51,314 --> 00:17:52,774
Then let's do it.
We got an offer to perform.

322
00:17:53,744 --> 00:17:54,714
Tell us more.

323
00:17:54,714 --> 00:17:55,974
Our performance at the Live House...

324
00:17:56,514 --> 00:17:59,074
The crowd liked us, so they asked if
we'd be interested in doing another.

325
00:17:59,554 --> 00:18:00,254
Let's do it.

326
00:18:00,254 --> 00:18:01,484
- All right!
- All right!

327
00:18:02,324 --> 00:18:04,054
That day I checked the classifieds
for job offers

328
00:18:04,054 --> 00:18:05,794
and went to three job interviews.

329
00:18:05,794 --> 00:18:09,194
For a dentist's receptionist,
a supermarket cashier,

330
00:18:09,194 --> 00:18:11,284
and a phone operator
for a pizza place.

331
00:18:11,734 --> 00:18:13,194
I got turned down by them all.

332
00:18:13,634 --> 00:18:15,464
What could they have found about me
that they didn't like?!

333
00:18:15,664 --> 00:18:17,964
I wanna know why you got fired
from your job in the first place?

334
00:18:18,234 --> 00:18:20,704
Well, because I started
making a habit of skipping work...

335
00:18:20,934 --> 00:18:23,804
But at the interviews
I told them in clear terms

336
00:18:23,804 --> 00:18:25,074
that I will take work seriously this time.

337
00:18:25,214 --> 00:18:27,674
Then you told them that you got fired
because you skipped work?!

338
00:18:27,674 --> 00:18:28,644
You're such a fool!

339
00:18:29,684 --> 00:18:33,054
You've gotta realize, if you take
just any job that you can get,

340
00:18:33,054 --> 00:18:35,114
you'll end up with the same result.

341
00:18:35,384 --> 00:18:37,414
Why not look for a job
that suits you better?

342
00:18:37,724 --> 00:18:39,214
What would be a job that suits me?

343
00:18:39,854 --> 00:18:41,154
Well, maybe not specifically
one that suits you.

344
00:18:41,424 --> 00:18:45,694
Any job will do as long as
it's a job you enjoy doing.

345
00:18:46,194 --> 00:18:48,434
If the workplace deals with
things you like,

346
00:18:48,434 --> 00:18:49,624
you'd be more motivated,
don't you think?

347
00:18:50,264 --> 00:18:52,634
When you were working
for Mr. Mizukoshi,

348
00:18:52,634 --> 00:18:55,704
you were surrounded by nice things
and you wore those pretty clothes.

349
00:18:55,704 --> 00:18:59,234
You seemed so alive at that job.
Why not look for another job like that?

350
00:19:00,814 --> 00:19:03,074
I see. That makes sense.
She's right.

351
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:06,314
I wonder how Mr. Mizukoshi is doing.

352
00:19:06,484 --> 00:19:08,074
Never mind Mr. Mizukoshi!

353
00:19:08,624 --> 00:19:09,884
But I sometimes think about him.

354
00:19:10,024 --> 00:19:13,524
I don't mind telling you now,
but I kinda had a crush on him.

355
00:19:13,524 --> 00:19:15,994
You don't have to tell me. I could tell.

356
00:19:16,524 --> 00:19:19,694
But, you know, taking Mr. Mizukoshi
and Takumi into consideration,

357
00:19:19,694 --> 00:19:20,684
you have a thing for long hair,
don't you?

358
00:19:21,334 --> 00:19:22,404
No way!

359
00:19:22,404 --> 00:19:24,034
What's with your overreacting?

360
00:19:24,034 --> 00:19:26,094
Because you're saying strange things!

361
00:19:26,234 --> 00:19:29,974
Strange? I prefer men
with short hair...

362
00:19:29,974 --> 00:19:32,514
You have it wrong!
Mr. Asano had short hair!

363
00:19:32,514 --> 00:19:34,274
- Asano?
- And so did Shoji!

364
00:19:38,114 --> 00:19:41,384
Well, I think his hair is pretty long.

365
00:19:41,924 --> 00:19:45,114
Yeah? Well, I guess that wouldn't be
considered short.

366
00:19:45,754 --> 00:19:47,314
Seeing that you're comfortable
talking about him,

367
00:19:47,824 --> 00:19:48,854
I guess you're over him now.

368
00:19:51,434 --> 00:19:53,924
It would be nice if you could find
a boyfriend soon. With long hair.

369
00:19:55,104 --> 00:19:59,054
There was just no way that
I could talk to Nana about Takumi.

370
00:20:00,704 --> 00:20:04,404
Being who he is, I couldn't even
tell Jun-chan about him.

371
00:20:04,774 --> 00:20:06,364
I wasn't able to discuss him
with anyone.

372
00:20:07,984 --> 00:20:10,504
I've never had that experience
with love, and it was very painful.

373
00:20:12,084 --> 00:20:14,244
Shoji, are you moving?

374
00:20:17,784 --> 00:20:19,624
What?! Shoji's moving in
with Sachiko?!

375
00:20:20,094 --> 00:20:22,214
They're such a lovey-dovey couple.

376
00:20:22,494 --> 00:20:27,624
That's nice. I envy them.
They seem so young.

377
00:20:28,734 --> 00:20:30,164
You're right.

